beer.beer_description:
During the golden age of sail, rounding Cape Horn was the ultimate test of character. On an annual mission to supply Aussie wheat to Europe, countless sailors took on this challenge during the "Great Grain Races". Those that survived were known as Mollyhawks. 

Our new Aussie Wheat Ale is an ode to those sailors, packed full of Aussie wheat. Its naturally hazy appearance conceals big juicy tropical fruit and fresh citrus notes.
